- **Description**: When a member's epoch is bumped during rebalancing, a consumer might simultaneously attempt to commit offsets using its old epoch. The current tests don't verify that offset commits from members with outdated epochs are correctly rejected with FENCED_MEMBER_EPOCH, preventing the coordinator from accepting stale offsets. This can result in incorrect offset tracking if a consumer commits with a stale epoch before realizing it has been fenced.
- **Proposed Test**:
  ```java
  @Test
  public void testOffsetCommitRejectedWhenMemberEpochBumped() throws Exception {
      GroupMetadataManagerTestContext context = new GroupMetadataManagerTestContext.Builder()
          .build();

      String groupId = "test-group";
      String memberId = Uuid.randomUuid().toString();
      String topicName = "test-topic";

      // Member joins group and receives epoch 1
      ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData joinRequest = new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
          .setGroupId(groupId)
          .setMemberId(memberId)
          .setMemberEpoch(0)
          .setRebalanceTimeoutMs(5000)
          .setSubscribedTopicNames(List.of(topicName))
          .setTopicPartitions(List.of());

      CoordinatorResult<ConsumerGroupHeartbeatResponseData, CoordinatorRecord> joinResult =
          context.groupMetadataManager.consumerGroupHeartbeat(requestContext(), joinRequest);

      int firstEpoch = joinResult.response().memberEpoch();

      // Member receives new epoch due to rebalance
      ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData heartbeatRequest = new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
          .setGroupId(groupId)
          .setMemberId(memberId)
          .setMemberEpoch(firstEpoch)
          .setRebalanceTimeoutMs(5000)
          .setSubscribedTopicNames(List.of(topicName))
          .setTopicPartitions(List.of());

      CoordinatorResult<ConsumerGroupHeartbeatResponseData, CoordinatorRecord> rebalanceResult =
          context.groupMetadataManager.consumerGroupHeartbeat(requestContext(), heartbeatRequest);

      int newEpoch = rebalanceResult.response().memberEpoch();
      assertTrue(newEpoch > firstEpoch, "Member epoch should increase during rebalance");

      // Member attempts to commit offset with OLD epoch (race condition)
      OffsetCommitRequestData offsetCommitRequest = new OffsetCommitRequestData()
          .setGroupId(groupId)
          .setMemberId(memberId)
          .setGenerationIdOrMemberEpoch(firstEpoch)  // Using old epoch
          .addTopic(new OffsetCommitRequestData.OffsetCommitRequestTopic()
              .setName(topicName)
              .addPartition(new OffsetCommitRequestData.OffsetCommitRequestPartition()
                  .setPartitionIndex(0)
                  .setCommittedOffset(100)
              )
          );

      CoordinatorResult<OffsetCommitResponseData, CoordinatorRecord> commitResult =
          context.groupMetadataManager.commitOffset(requestContext(), offsetCommitRequest);

      // Should reject with FENCED_MEMBER_EPOCH
      assertEquals(Errors.FENCED_MEMBER_EPOCH.code(),
          commitResult.response().topics().get(0).partitions().get(0).errorCode());

      context.close();
  }
